QuestDB Router (Horizontal Scaling Layer)
Overview

This project is a high-performance network routing layer for a horizontally scaled QuestDB cluster. It sits between clients and multiple QuestDB nodes and is responsible for routing, load balancing, and query/data distribution across the cluster.

It supports two primary protocols:

ILP (Influx Line Protocol) → write-heavy ingestion path
PGWire (PostgreSQL wire protocol) → SQL read/write queries

The system acts as a smart proxy + shard router, not a database itself.

Core Problem

QuestDB natively runs as a single-node high-performance time-series database. This project extends it into a distributed system by introducing:

Horizontal write scaling via sharding
Controlled read routing
Connection pooling and backend health awareness
Deterministic routing based on time-series keys
