Routing Model
1. ILP Routing (Write Path)

ILP lines are parsed and routed deterministically:

trades,symbol=AAPL,exchange=NASDAQ price=123.4 1712345678900

Routing logic:

Extract measurement + tags
Compute shard key (e.g. symbol)
Apply consistent hash:
shard = hash(symbol) % N
Forward raw ILP line to selected QuestDB node

Key properties:

Stateless routing
Zero or low allocation parsing
High throughput ingestion path
2. PGWire Routing (SQL Path)

The router accepts PostgreSQL wire protocol connections and acts as a proxy/coordinator.

Query types:

Simple queries (single shard)
SELECT * FROM trades WHERE symbol = 'AAPL'

→ routed to a single shard if key is present

Aggregations (multi-shard fan-out)
SELECT count(*) FROM trades

→ broadcast to all shards, merge results

Complex queries (future work)
SELECT * FROM trades t JOIN orders o ...

→ requires distributed execution layer (not MVP)

System Components
1. ILP Parser
Zero-copy parsing over &[u8]
Extracts:
measurement
tags
fields
timestamp
2. Shard Router
Consistent hashing ring
Maps symbol/table → node
Maintains cluster topology
3. Connection Pool
Persistent TCP pools per QuestDB node
Backpressure handling
Retry and failover logic
4. PGWire Proxy Layer
Accepts PostgreSQL connections
Parses minimal query metadata
Routes or fans out queries
5. Metadata Service (optional future component)
Stores shard mappings
Node health tracking
Rebalancing logic
Design Goals
Performance
Millions of writes/sec ingestion target
Minimal allocations in hot path
Zero-copy parsing wherever possible
Reliability
Node health checks
Automatic failover routing
Backpressure handling
Scalability
Horizontal scaling via shard addition
Stateless router instances
Deterministic routing logic
Observability
Prometheus metrics
Query latency tracking
Per-node throughput tracking
Technology Stack
Rust (Tokio runtime) → core data plane
Pingora (optional) → connection handling / proxy abstraction
Bytes → buffer management
AHash → fast hashing
DashMap → concurrent state
Moka → caching shard maps
Tracing + Prometheus → observability
Key Constraints
ILP is write-only → no query execution needed
PGWire is read/write → partial routing only
No distributed storage layer is implemented (QuestDB remains storage engine)
Router is stateless in MVP (except cache)
MVP Scope
Must have:
ILP ingestion routing
Consistent hashing shard selection
TCP proxy to QuestDB nodes
Basic PGWire passthrough
Node health checks
Should have:
Load balancing policies
Metrics + observability
Connection pooling
Future:
Distributed SQL execution
Rebalancing / resharding
Schema-aware routing
Multi-tenant isolation
Mental Model

Think of this system as:

NGINX for QuestDB
but with data-aware routing logic
and eventually partial distributed database behavior